{"_id":"0ohHDygmlDDNkqj5","name":"Navigate","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/navigate.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Finding your way quickly with maps, charts and tables, orienteering, instruments, or dead reckoning.</p>","base":10,"value":10,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"2VZK7OjNGkegDyi2","name":"HUMINT","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/humint.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Human intelligence. This obtains information about a subject&mdash;especially information the subject would rather conceal&mdash;through observation, conversation, or examining patterns of behavior and relationships. Use HUMINT to recognize signs of dishonesty from verbal cues and body language, gauge attitude and intentions, cultivate sources of information about a subject, determine what it would take to get a subject to cooperate, or recognize clues of what a subject wants to conceal. HUMINT can notice signs of mental illness, but Psychotherapy would be needed to diagnose and treat a specific malady. If your Agent also has Criminology, HUMINT can be used to compile a psychological profile to help find a subject. A subject who deliberately tries to deceive your Agent can attempt a Persuade test to oppose your Agent&rsquo;s HUMINT (see OPPOSED TESTS on page 45).</p>","base":10,"value":10,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"8WoPc5WjTNcdSL9H","name":"Pharmacy","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/pharmacy.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Knowledge of drugs, from their ingredients and creation, to their effects, uses, and misuses. Use it to identify and produce medicines and antidotes&mdash;as well as poisons. Identifying a drug requires at least 20% skill. Preparing a particularly powerful drug safely, such as one with psychoactive effects, requires at least 40% skill or a successful roll. Misusing Pharmacy is a quick way to kill a patient (see POISON AND DISEASE on page 60).</p>","base":0,"value":0,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"BWDOkCqZ7e5iNeHA","name":"Heavy Machinery","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/heavy_machinery.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Safe operation of a tractor, crane, bulldozer, tank, heavy truck, or other big machine in a crisis.</p>","base":10,"value":10,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"C2dlI0cv3U1tmg8N","name":"Dodge","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/dodge.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Evading danger through instinct and reflexes. Use Dodge to avoid an attack. Against firearms and explosives, Dodge is only useful to get to cover (see DODGING RANGED ATTACKS on page 54).</p>","base":30,"value":30,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Ctmt411Amqa44MdY","name":"Stealth","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/stealth.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Concealing your presence or activities. Use it to hide a pistol, camouflage a position, conceal a microphone, leave an envelope at a dead drop unobserved, pick a pocket, move silently, follow without being seen, or blend into a crowd. An Agent attempting Stealth can be detected only by an opposing Alertness or Search skill (see OPPOSED TESTS on page 45).</p>","base":10,"value":10,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"DQ4wMeoP2xhC3mVq","name":"Accounting","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/accounting.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>The study of finance and business. Use it to sift through financial records for anomalies, such as a hidden bank account or money launderin</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","base":10,"value":10,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"DXNRlh0CYwH500zA","name":"Law","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/law.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Using laws and courts to your Agent&rsquo;s advantage. Use it to get your Agent&rsquo;s way in court, to determine the correct procedures for handling evidence in a prosecution or a civil case (and how to undermine them), to bullshit your Agent&rsquo;s way out of legal trouble, or to minimize legal risks. The Law skill applies to your Agent&rsquo;s native country; using it with another country&rsquo;s laws requires special training (see page 30).</p>","base":0,"value":0,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EvQcT5iv6e2Get2B","name":"Psychotherapy","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/psychotherapy.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>The diagnosis and treatment of mental illness. Use it to identify a mental disorder, help a patient recover, talk someone down when a disorder begins to take over, and treat mental illness in the long term. You cannot use Psychotherapy on yourself. Using Psychotherapy to aid someone who suffered exposure to Unnatural forces might cost the therapist SAN; see THREATS TO SAN on page 67.</p>","base":10,"value":10,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"I3TbUwdFjxSbiWJG","name":"Ride","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/ride.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Handling, training, and riding an animal&mdash;horses, donkeys, camels, whatever. Exotic mounts may need special training (see page 30). Use it to keep safe on an animal in a crisis and to keep riding animals safe, calm, and healthy.</p>","base":10,"value":10,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"IVJlPnvpO0xLUuja","name":"Forensics","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/forensics.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Gathering detailed information and evidence using forensic equipment. Use it to record biometric data, determine details about a weapon used or the accelerant that started a fire, discern crucial clues that an ordinary searcher wouldn&rsquo;t recognize, clean a scene of incriminating evidence, or collect, analyze, and compare fingerprints and DNA samples.</p>","base":0,"value":0,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"IhFO9wVrCu1V7MiS","name":"Anthropology","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/anthropology.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>The study of living human cultures. Use it to understand morals, religious beliefs, customs, and mores, and to identify (but not translate) obscure languages. Where History is about the distant past and Archeology studies physical remains, Anthropology is about the behaviors of living cultures and how they relate to each other and the past.</p>","base":0,"value":0,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"MTEZ4gQD7UKtUN9L","name":"First Aid","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/first_aid.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>The initial treatment and stabilization of of injuries. Use it to help a character recover lost Hit Points. By comparison, Surgery corrects a severe wound and Medicine ensures long-term recovery. (See HEALING on page 55.)</p>","base":10,"value":10,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Or2gpjhBPTyIHtm0","name":"Athletics","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/athletics.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Your Agent trains to get the most out of his or her strength and agility. Strength and Dexterity cover raw physical power and manual dexterity; the Athletics skill represents long practice doing things like running, jumping, climbing, and throwing.</p>\n<p>Use Athletics to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Outrun someone (see OPPOSED TESTS on page 45).</li>\n<li>Jump an intimidating gap.</li>\n<li>Climb in a crisis.</li>\n<li>Land safely in a fall of up to three meters.</li>\n<li>Hit a target with a thrown knife or put a grenade exactly on target.</li>\n<li>Catch something without warning, such as intercepting a thrown grenade.</li>\n</ul>","base":30,"value":30,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"RuL1H39Oj4FcBdvI","name":"Survival","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/survival.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Knowledge of the natural world. Use it to find tracks and trails, plan an expedition, predict weather, recognize when fauna or flora are unusual, use the environment to gather other information, or find food, water, and shelter.</p>","base":10,"value":10,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"TAN0YADFbOdxZDvB","name":"Unnatural","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/unnatural.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Knowledge of the fundamental, mind-rending secrets of the universe. Use it to remember, recognize, or research facts about the things humans consider unnatural. This goes far beyond the occult, because the Unnatural skill represents things that are real. Use it to sift through the darkest parts of myth and folklore and recognize which of it is true. Your Agent&rsquo;s SAN score can never be higher than 99 minus his or her Unnatural skill rating.</p>","base":0,"value":0,"canimprove":false,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"UX73FP2uKRBVUnBB","name":"Surgery","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/surgery.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>The treatment of an injury or abnormality by invasive means. By comparison, First Aid keeps a patient alive until surgery is possible and Medicine ensures longterm recovery. (See HEALING on page 55.)</p>","base":0,"value":0,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"VzbZzMNd2NI0CvFm","name":"SIGINT","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/sigint.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Signals intelligence. It encompasses encryption, communications intelligence, electronic intelligence, surveillance of radio and digital communications, and the making and breaking of codes. It is often used in conjunction with Computer Science for hacking, and with Craft (Electrician) for installing bugs and wiretaps.</p>","base":0,"value":0,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"X6xSW29nmZLWcqz8","name":"Occult","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/occult.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>The study of the supernatural as understood by human traditions, including things like conspiracy theories, fringe science, and cryptozoology. Use Occult to examine and deduce the intent of a ritual, or to identify occult traditions, groups, grimoires, tools, symbols, or legends. Occult can never tell an Agent what&rsquo;s genuinely unnatural and what&rsquo;s just superstition or mythology. That&rsquo;s the province of the Unnatural skill.</p>","base":10,"value":10,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"b3h9Jstjj8KDssQD","name":"Drive","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/drive.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Handling an automobile or a motorcycle safely in a crisis. Unless the Handler says otherwise, every Agent has a driver&rsquo;s license and can drive a car safely in normal conditions. Use this skill to keep a vehicle safe in a high-speed pursuit or on dangerous terrain.</p>","base":20,"value":20,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"cy6fvWXAB1Dz2PKt","name":"Criminology","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/criminology.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Knowledge of criminal and conspiratorial behavior. Use it to identify and predict criminal behavior, deduce relationships between members of a conspiracy, analyze criminal activity, examine witness statements, or know whom to talk to in the criminal underground.</p>","base":10,"value":10,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"fh2NVcniXPIPUx7I","name":"Demolitions","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/demolitions.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Safe handling of explosives in a crisis. Use it to disarm a bomb, set a charge to destroy a target remotely, jury-rig an explosive from supplies at the hardware store, or analyze a blast to determine exactly what caused it. Failure when handling a bomb means your Agent needs more time. If it&rsquo;s a crisis that requires a roll, a fumble means an accidental explosion.</p>","base":0,"value":0,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"hSTg8NjAos3IrNBL","name":"Heavy Weapons","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/heavy_weapons.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Safe and accurate use of man-portable heavy ordnance such as machine guns and rocket launchers. Use Heavy Weapons to suppress enemies, or destroy a vehicle in combat.</p>","base":0,"value":0,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"iGAR2siJrhR1n6Pe","name":"Persuade","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/persuade.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Changing another&rsquo;s deeply-held decision or desire. Use Persuade to get your Agent&rsquo;s way when the subject is so stubborn, what your Agent wants is so valuable, or the deception is so flagrant that Charisma isn&rsquo;t enough. With Persuade, your Agent might convince a witness that what she saw was innocuous and not unnatural, talk a detective into helping you cover up evidence for the greater good, or draw useful intelligence out of an unwilling subject. This skill also allows your Agent to resist persuasion and interrogation in opposed Persuade rolls (see OPPOSED TESTS on page 45).</p>","base":20,"value":20,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"lCj52ePrQbjMXi7T","name":"Medicine","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/medicine.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>The study and treatment of injury and illness. Use it to diagnose the cause of an injury, disease, or poisoning, identify abnormalities such as toxins or diseases, identify the cause and approximate time of death, identify the type of weapon used to kill a victim, identify a dead person&rsquo;s last meal, or prescribe proper long-term care. By comparison, First Aid keeps a patient alive until surgery is possible and Surgery corrects a severe wound. (See HEALING on page 55).</p>","base":0,"value":0,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"nDG9Aslg2XuhmMAO","name":"Alertness","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/alertness.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Alertness detects danger. Use it to hear a safety being switched off, to understand the mumbling on the other side of a wall, to spot the bulge of a pistol hidden under a jacket, or to catch someone who is trying to escape notice using Stealth.</p>","base":20,"value":20,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"o2T8rAdGvoFZWSyE","name":"Archeology","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/archeology.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>The study of the physical remains of human cultures. Use it to analyze the way of life of a people from ruins, to determine the age of an artifact, to tell a genuine artifact from a fake, and to identify (but not translate) human languages. Where Anthropology is about living cultures and History is a broad study of the past, Archeology discerns meaning from the remains of peoples long dead.</p>","base":0,"value":0,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"o9WpYEdw9TeSGzIe","name":"Bureaucracy","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/bureucracy.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Manipulating the rules and personalities that govern an organization. Use it to locate and borrow supplies, convince an official to provide information or resources, gain credentials for access to a restricted area, or keep the hospital from delving too deeply into the source of your injuries.</p>","base":10,"value":10,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"p5gCogwRjvIetTQa","name":"Artillery","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/artillery.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Safe and accurate use of mortars, missiles, howitzers, tank cannons, and other heavy gunnery. Use it to destroy troops or a hard target in battle.</p>","base":0,"value":0,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"p77beSpGDZP6sefx","name":"Unarmed Combat","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/unarmed_combat.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Self-defense. A fight between untrained combatants often involves more shoving and shouting than real violence. Use Unarmed Combat to hurt or kill an opponent with your Agent&rsquo;s bare hands (or feet, elbows, teeth, or head).</p>","base":40,"value":40,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"pe90v9Hw2eBfUj1g","name":"Melee Weapons","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/melee_weapons.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Lethal use of melee weapons in combat. Use it to hurt or kill an opponent with a knife, axe, club, or other weapon.</p>","base":30,"value":30,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"qepiw9hV7YtwvLDI","name":"Search","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/search.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Finding things that are concealed or obscured from plain sight. Searching a scene may not require the Search skill, only time and effort, or a sufficiently high INT. Use Search to find an object that was hidden with the Stealth skill, or is otherwise so well hidden or disguised that it needs an expert. The Handler may roll the Search attempt so you don&rsquo;t know whether your Agent succeeded or failed.</p>","base":20,"value":20,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"vKi32H8nwf8gW8Dg","name":"Computer Science","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/computer_science.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Deep knowledge of computers, computer systems, and the programs that run them. Use it to recover erased or encrypted data, protect documents from easy access, implant software to hijack a computer system, clone a phone&rsquo;s SIM card, identify flaws in a security system, impersonate users, or falsify data. It is often complemented by Craft skills like Electrician and Microelectronics.</p>","base":0,"value":0,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"xkapZF7Xy1bD5IXQ","name":"Firearms","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/firearms.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Safe and accurate shooting with small arms in combat. Use it to hit a target despite the adrenaline, panic, and shock of violence interfering with hand-eye coordination.</p>","base":20,"value":20,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"zJAIL41kjMx6RCXw","name":"History","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/history.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Uncovering facts and theories about human antiquity. Use it to remember or find a key fact about the distant past, recognize an obscure reference, or comb a database or library for information that nobody without your deep education could find. While Anthropology is about living cultures and Archeology studies the meaning of ancient relics, History is a broad study of humanity.</p>","base":10,"value":10,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"zbZu96XHtgpWT2y4","name":"Disguise","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/disguise.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Alter your Agent&rsquo;s appearance, voice, posture, body language, and mannerisms to avoid recognition without drawing attention.</p>","base":10,"value":10,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"zzCl14hYheGqykcA","name":"Swim","type":"Skill","img":"systems/delta-green-alt/assets/icons/swim.svg","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Most Agents can swim for leisure. Use the Swim skill in a dangerous crisis: going a long distance in choppy water, keeping a friend from drowning, or getting to a boat before the tentacled thing below grabs you.</p>","base":20,"value":20,"canimprove":true,"failcheck":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J8nyE3UZJoth2Wyb":3},"flags":{}}
